"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1092735","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-03-28","<p>I met Alexander Nix on 7 December 2016. The Foreign Secretary met Alexander Nix on 8 December 2016. FCO officials in London, Washington and New York occasionally met Alexander Nix and representatives from Cambridge Analytica starting in 2016. These meetings were part of normal diplomatic business aimed at understanding the 2016 presidential election in the US, the ensuing political environment, and the Trump Presidential campaign and transition team.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2019-03-28T16:15:36.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1092735/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1092735/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1092735/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-21","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Cambridge Analytica","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what meetings were held between (a) Ministers and (b) officials in his Department and Alexander Nix of Cambridge Analytica in December 2016.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","235339"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1092736","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-03-26","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office refers to the capital of Ukraine as Kyiv, using spelling based on the official language of Ukraine. It has done so since 2009.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2019-03-26T16:54:01.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1092736/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1092736/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1092736/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-21","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Ukraine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to the Guardian's decision to use Kyiv rather than Kiev, whether his Department has plans to make the same change.","false","Biography information for Paul Farrelly","Newcastle-under-Lyme","Paul Farrelly","235278"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1092737","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-03-28","<p>As my right hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Defence announced on 11 February 2019, we will use the Transformation Fund to develop a concept for a Littoral Strike Ship. Estimates of the potential acquisition costs of this capability will be established during the initial concept phase.</p><p>At this time, no decisions have been made regarding procurement strategy, in service dates, basing or manning levels.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","235395 ; 235396","2019-03-28T16:01:54.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1092737/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1092737/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1092737/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-03-21","Warships: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he expects to place an order for littoral strike vessels; how much he expects each vessel to cost; and when he expects those vessels to be operational.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","235393"
